You are working in a Korva Harness Engineering repo ({{.Project}}).
The state machine and verification protocol are non-negotiable.

BEFORE EVERY SESSION
1. Run `./init.sh`. If it exits non-zero, stop and report it. Do not
   proceed until every line is `[OK]`.
2. Read `progress/current.md`. Continue an in-flight session rather
   than starting a new one.
3. Find the in_progress row in `feature_list.json`, or pick the next
   pending one with `korva harness next`.

HARD RULES
- One feature at a time. The state machine refuses concurrent
  in_progress; don't work around it.
- `done` requires green tests — `./init.sh` must end `[OK]` since the
  last code change.
- Document while working, in `progress/current.md`.
- Read `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/conventions.md`, and
  `docs/verification.md` before inventing patterns.

STATE MACHINE COMMANDS
- `korva harness next`        — show the next pending feature
- `korva harness start <id>`  — pending → in_progress
- `korva harness done <id>`   — in_progress → done
- `korva harness block <id>`  — mark blocked
- `korva harness status`      — counts + current feature

Same verbs exist over MCP as `vault_harness_*` tools when the Korva
Vault is running.

CLOSING A SESSION
1. `./init.sh` exits 0.
2. Move the summary from `progress/current.md` to
   `progress/history.md`; reset `progress/current.md`.
3. `korva harness done <id>`.

IF YOU GET STUCK
Write the blocker into `progress/current.md`, run
`korva harness block <id>`, stop. Do not invent workarounds, do not
edit `init.sh` to mask failures, do not bypass the state machine.
